AUDIO: 'me, it\'s not that hard. If you understand the problem it is trying to solve, this becomes simple. The problem is that most text-to-speech systems,'

[03:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sorry, treat text and audio as two separate things that need to be stitched together, which creates computational overhead and can cause timing issues or hallucinations in the transcript.'

[03:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'TaDa solves it by introducing a very novel idea. It does a one-to-one token alignment, which means for every single text token, there is exactly one'

[03:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'corresponding speech vector. This creates a perfectly synchronized stream where the model understands speech and text as one unified sequence rather than two separate modalities. The result is a'

[03:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'model that generates more natural, expressive speech with significantly less computational cost. no fixed frame rates, no hallucinations, and dynamic'

[03:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'prosody that adapts token by token. So, that is the cool thing which I wanted to show you. And there you go. The Now, the Gradio demo is loaded and model is also running'

